Why does the @emph{database} throw an error in the @code{expand-clones} method? There are no database calls there. Hint: whenever possible Clojure tries to use @emph{lazy collections}, meaning they are not generated straight off but only on an as-requested basis. This is part of why and how it is possible to work with infinite data series. The other clue is that the database connection defaults to recycling open cursors after 10 minutes, if a new candidate is not requested in more than 10 minutes the database is going to kill the connection. We could force Clojure's hand and wrap the call to @code{storage/identify-candidates!} in a @code{doall} block, making sure that all candidates are in memory before we start the @code{expand}. However, we would still have the ramp antipattern in there, so the time per candidate is still going to grow and ultimately something else is going to break for us if we @emph{do} try to throw Real Big Data (TM) onto this algorithm. Most likely our sanity will be the first to go.

